<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id747182af-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s23110"><num value="23110">§ 23110.</num><heading> Service of process</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The corporation shall have a designated agent in the District of Columbia to receive service of process for the corporation. Notice to or service on the agent is notice to or service on the corporation.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id747182b0-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1314">112 Stat. 1314</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
